Reasoning: The paper investigates the achievable information rate of PSK over fading channels without CSI, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The paper also considers temporal correlation and spectral density functions, which are related to signal processing and statistical inference (cs.SI). The study of low-SNR asymptotics is relevant to network information theory (cs.NI) and game theory (cs.GT).
